President Obama called President Alassane Ouattara to congratulate him on becoming the democratically elected President of Cote d'Ivoire. They discussed the importance of uniting the country, restarting the economy, restoring security, and reforming the security forces. President Obama expressed his admiration for the potential of the Ivorian people and emphasized the need to reestablish trade and assistance relationships to boost the private sector. They also agreed on the importance of investigating alleged atrocities and holding perpetrators accountable, with support for the United Nations commission of inquiry and the International Criminal Court. President Obama welcomed President Ouattara's commitment to security and advancing the aspirations of all Ivorians, and assured the United States' strong partnership in forming an inclusive government, promoting reunification and reconciliation, and addressing the humanitarian situation.